# DELACED — Issue I

## Project
A single-page interactive editorial built in plain HTML, CSS, and vanilla JS.
No frameworks. No build tools. Open index.html directly in a browser.

## Mood
Luxury independent magazine. Cream paper, lace, ballet, burgundy.
Nostalgia, quiet longing, abandoned ambitions. Feminine without cliché.

## Palette
- Background: #f7f2eb (warm cream)
- Secondary: #f2ede4, #e8dece, #c4b8a8
- Accent: #6b1a2a (burgundy), #d4a0a8 (dusty pink), #b8924a (gold)
- Text: #2a2218 (ink), #7a6e62 (muted)

## Typography
All serif — Cormorant Garamond from Google Fonts (weights 300, 400; italic variants).
No sans-serif anywhere.

## Animation rules
- Nothing bounces, pops, or scales aggressively
- Everything: drifts, floats, breathes, unravels
- Use opacity + transform + SVG path animation
- Scroll-driven via IntersectionObserver and scroll event listeners
- Target 60fps, requestAnimationFrame for canvas work
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion

## Sections (in order)
1. Hero — "I wanted to become everything." / "and somewhere I forgot."
2. Ballet — ankle + pointe shoe, lace ribbon unravels on scroll
3. Ambitions — layered handwritten words (law, dance, medicine...) in background
4. Fish — 3 illustrated fish on canvas (butterfly koi, ranchu, koi), leave lace trails
5. Debate — dark section, ornate ceiling SVG, slow 2–3° rotation on scroll
6. Envelope — opens automatically at 60% viewport, letter rises, "... remember me?" fades in

## Lace
Lace is the visual language throughout — dividers, corners, overlays, trails.
As the page progresses, lace slowly unravels. SVG-drawn, never images.

##  tagline only at the end after envelope opens and letter gets pulled out
"... remember me?" — always in dusty pink (#d4a0a8), italic, small, discovered not announced.

## What to avoid
- Generic fade-up animations
- Elastic easing
- Overcrowded layouts — one visual, one sentence, one emotion per section
- Any sans-serif font
- Borders or UI chrome that feels like a website
